			<p class="bodySubTitle">Who Can Apply?</p>
			<p class="bodyText">
				If you want to apply for Medicaid, you must call for an appointment at the MAP office nearest you. If you are unable to go there, you may have a representative apply on your behalf. 
				However, you must sign an application and provide certain information about yourself and your family. 
				The Certification Unit at the MAP Office will determine your eligibility. Eligibility for Medicaid is based on your residency status, family income, resources and other factors. 
				The MAP office can advise you about specific documents to bring to your appointment and additional requirements.
			</p>
